subSections.title: Glyph origin
subSections.text:
{{Han etyl}}
{{liushu|p}} — a cattle head with horns. In the oracle bone script, {{lang|zh|㞢}} and {{lang|zh|之}} are different characters. In early oracle bone script, {{lang|zh|㞢}} was borrowed to represent {{och-l|有|to have}}. In late oracle bone script, {{lang|zh|㞢}} was replaced by {{och-l|又|right hand}}. Post-Qin dictionaries often treat {{lang|zh|㞢}} as an ancient form of {{och-l|之}}.
